Method Detail

parse

public static ResponseTypeSet parse(java.lang.String s)
                             throws ParseException
Parses a set of authorisation response types.

OpenID Connect specifies the following string vectors but this method will allow other orders as well to accommodate sloppy serialisers: 

 code
 token
 id_token
 id_token token
 code token
 code id_token token

Parameters:
s - Space-delimited list of one or more individual authorisation response types.
Returns:
The parsed authorisation response types set.
Throws:
ParseException - If the parsed string is null, empty or contains an invalid response type name.

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
Returns the canonical string representation of this set of authorisation response types.

The serialised set is guaranteed to have one of the following orders (to conform with the OpenID Connect spec): 

 code
 token
 id_token
 id_token token
 code token
 code id_token token

Overrides:
toString in class java.util.AbstractCollection<ResponseType>
Returns:
Space-delimited string representing the authorisation response types.
